			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Secondary copper, produced from recycled scrap, accounts for 40% of today's copper production. The carbon intensity of producing secondary copper can vary greatly. It can require up to 90% less energy than primary copper, but there is some overlap in the carbon intensity ranges. Secondary sulfides, which are formed by supergene secondary enrichment, are resistant to sulfuric leaching. Refined secondary copper production amounted to an estimated 4.15 million metric tons worldwide in 2021.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">利用回收废料生产的二次铜占当今铜产量的 40%。生产二级铜的碳强度差异很大。与原生铜相比，它所需的能源最多可减少 90%，但碳强度范围也有一些重叠。由超生二次富集形成的次生硫化物耐硫酸浸出。2021 年，全球精炼二级铜产量约为 415 万公吨。</common:generalComment>
